<sn><md>**Example 6.** The profit-principal of some principal is Tk. 5,500 in 3 years. If the profit is $\frac{3}{8}$ part of the principal, find the principal and the rate of profit.

**Solution:**

We know, Principal + Profit = Profit-principal<br>
i.e., $P + I = A$<br>
or, $P + \frac{3}{8}P = A$<br>
or, $\left(1 + \frac{3}{8}\right) \times P = 5,500$<br>
or, $\frac{11}{8} \times P = 5,500$

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-8

* or, $P = 5,500 \times \dfrac{8}{11}$

* $= \text{Tk. } \dfrac{5,500 \times 8}{11}$

* $= \text{Tk. } 4,000$

Therefore, Profit = Profit-principal $-$ Principal

* $= \text{Tk. } (5,500 - 4,000)$

* $= \text{Tk. } 1,500$

Again, we know, $I = Prn$

* or, $r = \dfrac{I}{Pn}$

* $= \dfrac{1,500}{4,000 \times 3}$

* $= \dfrac{1,500}{12,000}$

* $= \dfrac{1}{8}$

* $= \dfrac{1 \times 100}{8 \times 100}$

* $= \dfrac{100}{8} \times \frac{1}{100}$

* $= 12.5\%$

* $= 12\frac{1}{2}\%$

∴ Principal is **Tk. 4,000** and rate of profit is **$12\frac{1}{2}\%$**.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-4
**Where,**
| Symbol | Value |
|--------|-------|
| $P$ | Principal = Required |
| $I$ | Profit = Tk. 1,500 |
| $r$ | Rate of Profit = Required |
| $n$ | Time = 3 years |
| $A$ | Profit-principal = Tk. 5,500 |
:::
:::
</md></sn>